OL,7,F"People think that disabled people are
OL,8,Fincapable of doing things, but
OL,9,Factually it's quite often the outside
OL,10,Fworld and the system and the transport
OL,11,Fthat makes us feel more disabled than
OL,12,Fwe are because it stops us from doing
OL,13,Fthings."
OL,15,FMark Evers, Transport for London's
OL,16,FChief Customer Officer, said: "We're
OL,17,Fvery sorry for the stressful
OL,18,Fexperience that Zara suffered while
OL,19,Ftravelling with us.
