OL,5,Ctrain journey
OL,7,FReflecting on her journey, Zara said,
OL,8,F"it was quite a traumatic experience"
OL,9,Fand has lost trust in the
OL,10,Faccessibility of London's transport.
OL,12,FShe said: "I had about three panic
OL,13,Fattacks on that day."
OL,15,F"It's not fair because we don't choose
OL,16,Fto be disabled, but because they see
OL,17,Fus as a minority, they don't put us as
OL,18,Fa priority. And I think that's where
OL,19,Fthe problem is."
